As a Noun: 1. X-RAYS are a type of radiation that can pass through most solid materials. X-RAYS are used by doctors to take a picture and examine the bones or organs inside your body.
Note: 1. There appears to be no commonly used Auslan sign for X-RAY. If you know a sign for X-RAY used by you or other Auslan users (deaf people or interpreters) please go to "report missing sign" and supply details. Thank you.

General Definition: 1. To hit something rhythmically with something else, or any thing or any action directly or indirectly associated with this, such as a row of drums, and especially a xylophone.
As a Noun: 1.  A musical instrument made of a row of wooden bars of different lengths that you hit with a special hammer. English = xylophone.
